      • 2020-11-06 | Gator Cogitate
        - Python program that retrieves and analyzes statistics of a GitHub Repository.

        Summary

        Created: In-class spring 2019
        Written during a Software engineering class in 2020 by the entire class, this project is a free and open source tool written in Python. It is designed to evaluate the level of contributions for members of a GitHub repository. GatorCogitate generates a score for members based on a variety of metrics.

      • 2020-11-20 | Maze Programs
        - A collection of algorithms I have implemented in Python for drawing mazes.

        Summary

        Created: Personal continuation of a class project in spring 2018
        Started after my first final project in my first coding class, this program contains two working wall-adder algorithms that produce Perfect-2D-Orthogonal Mazes (perfect here means only one solution). It is run by a main program from which you can run both mazes. It has a handcrafted UI made with TKinter and has the option to save its mazes as images.
